---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy | HoundStack"
  description="The HoundStack privacy policy: what data the marketing site and product collect, how it is used, and the choices you have."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated July 6, 2026. Draft pending legal review.</p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        We collect what is needed to run the service and nothing speculative. We do not sell your
        data. We do not run advertising trackers on this site. Payment card data goes to Stripe
        and never touches our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>What this site collects</h2>
      <p>
        This marketing site uses Plausible Analytics, a privacy respecting tool that does not use
        cookies and does not track you across sites. We see aggregate page views and referral
        sources, not individual profiles. If you submit the contact or request access form, we
        receive the name, business name, email, and message you typed, and we use them to respond
        to you.
      </p>

      <h2>What the product collects</h2>
      <p>
        Accounts on app.houndstack.com store the business data you put into them: client and dog
        records, service addresses, schedules, visit history and photos, gate codes and access
        notes, hazard notes, invoices, and message history. This data belongs to the business that
        entered it. We process it to provide the service and for nothing else.
      </p>

      <h2>Payments</h2>
      <p>
        Payments are processed by Stripe under your own Stripe account. Card numbers are entered
        into and stored by Stripe directly and never reach HoundStack servers. Stripe's own
        privacy policy governs that data.
      </p>

      <h2>Subprocessors</h2>
      <p>
        We use a small set of service providers to run the product: Stripe (payments), Twilio
        (SMS), Google Maps (routing and navigation), Anthropic (AI features), and our hosting
        providers. Each receives only what its function requires.
      </p>

      <h2>Data isolation</h2>
      <p>
        HoundStack is multi tenant with row level isolation. Every record is scoped to a single
        business account at the database layer, and no other customer can access your data.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can export your data in one click at any time, request deletion of your account and
        its data, and unsubscribe from any non transactional email. Requests can be sent through
        the <a href="/contact">contact form</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes in a way that matters, account owners will be notified by email
        before the change takes effect.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(48px, 6vw, 80px);
  }
</style>
